OL,3,CSchoolboy attacked teacher with a
OL,4,Chammer in a 'sort of rage', court hears
OL,6,FThe trial at Exeter Crown Court has
OL,7,Fheard the schoolboy, who cannot be
OL,8,Fidentified for legal reasons, had
OL,9,Fmoments earlier allegedly attacked two
OL,10,Fother sleeping teenagers.
OL,12,F"As I opened the door, he then turned
OL,13,Ftowards me and struck me on the head
OL,14,Fwith a hammer," Mr Roffe-Silvester
OL,15,Ftold the court.
OL,17,F"Physically I stumbled backwards into
OL,18,Fthe corridor. There was a second blow
OL,19,F` I can't remember if it was before I
OL,20,Fstumbled back ` that's a little bit
OL,21,Fhazy for me."
